This is the recursive function that fails:

``` javascript
function totalServiceTime(stamps, acc = 0) {
  if (stamps.length === 0) {
    return acc;
  } else {
    const ts = _(stamps).minBy((s) => s.timestamp);
    const [current, next] = _(stamps)
        .partition((t) =>
          t.timestamp >= ts.timestamp
          && t.timestamp + t.duration <= ts.timestamp + ts.duration)
        .value();
    const endTs = Math.max(...current.map((t) => t.timestamp + t.duration));
    return totalServiceTime(next, acc + (endTs - ts.timestamp));
  }
}
```

Unfortunately, it fails on some traces, but so far it has been difficult to reproduce. @adriancole got the same error, but couldn't reproduce later...

If you set a breakpoint there somewhere, do you see whether `current` and/or `next` is changed from function cal to function call? If not, it results in an infinite loop. The interesting thing is to find the type of data that makes the function loop forever!

this is also hard to test, as ZipkinQueryServerFeatureTest doesn't have a classpath reference to the resources built by zipkin-ui. Ex. even if you set the following, it 404s

